After completing repairs to the parts of the ship he damaged, Celeron began to reprogramming the computer to recognize him as its owner.   As his computer ran a diagnostic on the ship&#39;s computers he decided to examine the engines and hull.

As Celeron entered the engine room, he saw numerous lifeless bodies.   The engine was in terrible shape; but he began an estimate on what parts he would need to replace.  There was 4 reactors, all of which seemed to be in perfect condition; only one of them was on.  The engineering console was in a easily decipherable language and apparently all of the primary energy conduits were online.  The rear section of the ship had no power running to it, probably to save power.

Celeron got a  message from his computer that the results of the reprogramming were in; Celeron returned to the bridge.

&quot;Username: Celeron now recognized as sole owner.  You have access to 80% of all information on all servers.  20% remains as encrypted information.  All ship functions are under your control.&quot;

&quot;Bring all servers online.&quot;

Some lights came on and the servers began to humm.  The door to the server room closed and locked.  The holotable lit up, and the same face appeared over it.

&quot;Welcome, I am Templar 1288.  Civilian defence and navigational AI.  All security systems are active.  I will now announce the damage report.  Shields: 100%  Hull Integrity: 48%  Engines 0%  Reactors 100%  Power Systems 90%  Internal Communications: Online External Communications: Offline Emergency Systems: offline....&quot;

&quot;End report.&quot;
&quot;Acknnowledged&quot;
&quot;Where are the remote controls for crewmembers.&quot;
&quot;All remote systems are accessed via com link or external audio receivers.&quot;
&quot;Deactivate external audio receivers.&quot;
&quot;Affirmative&quot;
&quot;Activate sound shielding&quot;
&quot;Done.&quot;
&quot;Is there an AR chamber aboard?&quot;
&quot;There are 23 AR chambers in the rear sections.&quot;
&quot;Reactivate power in those sections.&quot;
&quot;Afirmative....Power grid damaged in the rear.  2 AR chambers near the bridge are working.&quot;
&quot;Begin AR prep. move control from bridge to the room with the chamber, put security on high alert.&quot;
&quot;Aside from AR and Secrurity, enter power saving mode and begin charging all batteries.&quot;
&quot;Done.  Enjoy your nap Sir.&quot;
&quot;Humor...BAH!&quot;

As Celeron walked down the hallway, he could hear the doors closing and locking behind him.  As he entered the room.  He  noticed that these were the captain&#39;s quarters.  He looked into the chamber.  The captain was inside.  Celeron looked at the console.  The captain would awake in 4 solar cycles, no override.

&quot;Computer, activate and prep other chamber.  Seal this room. Transfer control to the other room.&quot;
&quot;Afirmative...&quot;
As Celeron walked to the other room, he remembered the computers he left in the server room.
&quot;Computer, Seal bridge, and server room.&quot;
&quot;This has already been done with the high security.&quot;
&quot;I&#39;ll remember that.&quot;
&quot;All orders carried out.&quot;

Celeron entered the other room.  Apparently this was the 1st officer&#39;s quarters.  There was no one in this chamber.  Celeron opened the door on the chamber.

&quot;Computer, seal door, deactivate all controls other then this room.&quot;
&quot;Affirmative&quot;
&quot;Activate AR chamber for 1/2 of a cycle.&quot;
&quot;Confirmed&quot;
&quot;Maintain a separate log of everything that happens while I&#39;m recharging.&quot;
&quot;Done&quot;
&quot;Good...&quot;

The door closed and Celeron powered down.




